Random-num-Perl
Description:

A perl script that selects a random number between 1 and 100 and guides a user to it.
Use:

    Make sure that you have perl installed, i.e perl -v

    Once you download the file, ensure that it has the right permissions to execute.

    The file executes Perl from /usr/bin/perl path. Change this to whichever path your perl command is posited e.g /usr/local/bin/perl

    Run the executable file "./random100.pl" and begin obeying the clues.
